{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775850001187,"sessionID":"ses_2871a038cffesMuBUUK1SL04AQ","part":{"id":"prt_d78e78523001YmIJ0yzPlqzdDP","messageID":"msg_d78e76499001PMat4XqnkLRXxY","sessionID":"ses_2871a038cffesMuBUUK1SL04AQ","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_7b8f5082975b4885afc167af","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-020: CLI pack 命令 — Delta Spec\n\n## Context\n\n- **Module:** cmd/cli\n- **Language:** Python\n- **Size:** M\n- **Base specs:** `cli-toolkit/design.md`, `cli-toolkit/spec.md`\n\n## Delta Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Workspace validation — not a directory\n\n#### Scenario: Workspace path exists but is a file\n- **GIVEN** the user provides `--workspace` pointing to a regular file (not a directory)\n- **WHEN** `PackRuntime._validate_workspace_structure` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` with a message indicating the path is not a directory\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Workspace validation — Java-specific\n\n#### Scenario: Java workspace without pom.xml\n- **GIVEN** `metadata.language` is `\"java\"`\n- **WHEN** no `pom.xml` exists in the workspace root directory\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` indicating `pom.xml` is required for Java projects\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Metadata loading with fallback chain\n\n#### Scenario: Primary metadata file exists\n- **GIVEN** `agent_metadata.yaml` exists in the workspace root\n- **WHEN** `MetadataService.load_metadata` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL load and parse `agent_metadata.yaml` as `AgentMetadata`\n\n#### Scenario: Primary missing, first fallback exists\n- **GIVEN** `agent_metadata.yaml` does not exist but `agent.yaml` exists in the workspace root\n- **WHEN** `MetadataService.load_metadata` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL load and parse `agent.yaml` as `AgentMetadata`\n\n#### Scenario: Primary and first fallback missing, second fallback exists\n- **GIVEN** neither `agent_metadata.yaml` nor `agent.yaml` exists, but `metadata.yaml` exists in the workspace root\n- **WHEN** `MetadataService.load_metadata` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL load and parse `metadata.yaml` as `AgentMetadata`\n\n#### Scenario: No metadata file exists — create from CLI options\n- **GIVEN** none of `agent_metadata.yaml`, `agent.yaml`, or `metadata.yaml` exist in the workspace root\n- **WHEN** `PackRuntime._load_or_create_metadata` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL create a new `AgentMetadata` instance using CLI-provided options and inferred defaults\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Metadata merge — CLI overrides\n\n#### Scenario: CLI `--agent-name` overrides existing metadata\n- **GIVEN** existing metadata has `agent_name: \"old-agent\"`\n- **WHEN** the user passes `--agent-name \"new-agent\"`\n- **THEN** `PackRuntime._apply_option_overrides` SHALL set `metadata.agent_name` to `\"new-agent\"`\n\n#### Scenario: CLI `--language` overrides existing metadata\n- **GIVEN** existing metadata has `language: \"python\"`\n- **WHEN** the user passes `--language \"java\"`\n- **THEN** the system SHALL update `metadata.language` to `\"java\"` and re-validate via Pydantic validators\n\n#### Scenario: CLI `--entrypoint` overrides existing metadata\n- **GIVEN** existing metadata has `entrypoint: \"python main.py\"`\n- **WHEN** the user passes `--entrypoint \"python app.py\"`\n- **THEN** the system SHALL update `metadata.entrypoint` to `\"python app.py\"`\n\n#### Scenario: CLI `--port` overrides existing metadata\n- **GIVEN** existing metadata has `port: 8080`\n- **WHEN** the user passes `--port 9090`\n- **THEN** the system SHALL update `metadata.port` to `9090`\n\n#### Scenario: CLI `--build-mode` overrides existing metadata\n- **GIVEN** existing metadata has `build_mode: \"local\"`\n- **WHEN** the user passes `--build-mode \"cloud\"`\n- **THEN** the system SHALL update `metadata.build_mode` to `\"cloud\"`\n\n#### Scenario: CLI `--description` overrides existing metadata\n- **GIVEN** existing metadata has `description: \"old description\"`\n- **WHEN** the user passes `--description \"new description\"`\n- **THEN** the system SHALL update `metadata.description` to `\"new description\"`\n\n#### Scenario: CLI option is None, metadata value preserved\n- **GIVEN** existing metadata has `agent_name: \"my-agent\"`\n- **WHEN** the user does NOT pass `--agent-name` (value is `None`)\n- **THEN** the system SHALL preserve `metadata.agent_name` as `\"my-agent\"`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Entrypoint inference — Python\n\n#### Scenario: Python entrypoint inferred from first .py file\n- **GIVEN** `metadata.entrypoint` is `None` and `language` is `\"python\"`\n- **WHEN** `PackRuntime._infer_entrypoint` runs and the workspace contains `main.py`\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return `\"python main.py\"` as the inferred entrypoint\n\n#### Scenario: Python entrypoint inferred from alternative .py file\n- **GIVEN** `metadata.entrypoint` is `None` and `language` is `\"python\"`\n- **WHEN** `PackRuntime._infer_entrypoint` runs and the workspace contains `app.py` but no `main.py`\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return `\"python app.py\"` as the inferred entrypoint\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Entrypoint inference — Java\n\n#### Scenario: Java entrypoint inferred as jar execution\n- **GIVEN** `metadata.entrypoint` is `None` and `language` is `\"java\"`\n- **WHEN** `PackRuntime._infer_entrypoint` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return `\"java -jar target/*.jar\"` or equivalent based on `pom.xml` analysis\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Entrypoint inference — failure\n\n#### Scenario: No entrypoint inferable\n- **GIVEN** `metadata.entrypoint` is `None` and no inferable entrypoint exists for the language\n- **WHEN** `PackRuntime._infer_entrypoint` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` indicating entrypoint could not be inferred and must be provided via `--entrypoint`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Python compatibility validation\n\n#### Scenario: Python workspace has requirements.txt\n- **GIVEN** `metadata.language` is `\"python\"` and `requirements.txt` exists in the workspace root\n- **WHEN** `PackRuntime._validate_python_compatibility` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL pass without error\n\n#### Scenario: Python workspace missing requirements.txt\n- **GIVEN** `metadata.language` is `\"python\"` and `metadata.requirements_file` is `\"requirements.txt\"`\n- **WHEN** `requirements.txt` does not exist in the workspace root\n- **WHEN** `PackRuntime._validate_python_compatibility` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` indicating the dependency file is missing\n\n#### Scenario: Python custom requirements file exists\n- **GIVEN** `metadata.language` is `\"python\"` and `metadata.requirements_file` is `\"deps.txt\"`\n- **WHEN** `deps.txt` exists in the workspace root\n- **WHEN** `PackRuntime._validate_python_compatibility` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL pass without error\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Java compatibility validation\n\n#### Scenario: Java workspace has valid pom.xml\n- **GIVEN** `metadata.language` is `\"java\"` and `pom.xml` exists with valid XML\n- **WHEN** `PackRuntime._validate_java_compatibility` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL pass without error\n\n#### Scenario: Java workspace has invalid pom.xml\n- **GIVEN** `metadata.language` is `\"java\"` and `pom.xml` exists but is not valid XML\n- **WHEN** `PackRuntime._validate_java_compatibility` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` indicating invalid `pom.xml`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Dependency processing — Python\n\n#### Scenario: Python dependencies processed from requirements.txt\n- **GIVEN** `metadata.language` is `\"python\"` and `requirements.txt` exists\n- **WHEN** `PackRuntime._process_python_dependencies` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL read and validate the contents of `requirements.txt`\n\n#### Scenario: Python custom requirements file processed\n- **GIVEN** `metadata.language` is `\"python\"` and `metadata.requirements_file` is `\"deps.txt\"`\n- **WHEN** `PackRuntime._process_python_dependencies` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL read and validate `deps.txt` instead of `requirements.txt`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Dependency processing — Java\n\n#### Scenario: Java dependencies processed from pom.xml\n- **GIVEN** `metadata.language` is `\"java\"` and `pom.xml` exists\n- **WHEN** `PackRuntime._process_java_dependencies` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL parse `pom.xml` to extract dependency information\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Dockerfile generation — Python\n\n#### Scenario: Generate Python Dockerfile when none exists\n- **GIVEN** `metadata.language` is `\"python\"` and no `Dockerfile` exists in the workspace\n- **WHEN** `PackRuntime._generate_dockerfile` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL call `_generate_python_dockerfile` and write the result to `{workspace}/Dockerfile`\n\n#### Scenario: Python Dockerfile includes required directives\n- **GIVEN** `PackRuntime._generate_python_dockerfile` is called with `metadata.port=8080` and `metadata.entrypoint=\"python main.py\"`\n- **WHEN** generating the Dockerfile content\n- **THEN** the output SHALL include: a base Python image, `WORKDIR`, copy of workspace files, `pip install -r requirements.txt`, `EXPOSE 8080`, and `CMD [\"python\", \"main.py\"]`\n\n#### Scenario: Existing Dockerfile is preserved\n- **GIVEN** a `Dockerfile` already exists in the workspace root\n- **WHEN** `PackRuntime._generate_dockerfile` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL NOT overwrite the existing `Dockerfile` and SHALL return the existing path\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Dockerfile generation — Java\n\n#### Scenario: Generate Java Dockerfile when none exists\n- **GIVEN** `metadata.language` is `\"java\"` and no `Dockerfile` exists in the workspace\n- **WHEN** `PackRuntime._generate_dockerfile` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL call `_generate_java_dockerfile` and write the result to `{workspace}/Dockerfile`\n\n#### Scenario: Java Dockerfile includes multi-stage build\n- **GIVEN** `PackRuntime._generate_java_dockerfile` is called with `metadata.port=8080`\n- **WHEN** generating the Dockerfile content\n- **THEN** the output SHALL include: a Maven build stage (copy `pom.xml`, run `mvn package`), a runtime stage with JAR execution, `EXPOSE 8080`, and `CMD` using `metadata.entrypoint`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Pack metadata update\n\n#### Scenario: Metadata updated after successful pack\n- **GIVEN** pack has completed successfully with resolved metadata and optional generated `Dockerfile`\n- **WHEN** `PackRuntime._update_pack_metadata` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL save `agent_metadata.yaml` with the final `entrypoint`, `language`, `port`, `build_mode`, `description`, and `dockerfile_path` (if generated)\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Output path preparation\n\n#### Scenario: Default output path is workspace root\n- **GIVEN** the user does NOT pass `--output`\n- **WHEN** `PackRuntime._prepare_output_path` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return the resolved workspace root as the output path\n\n#### Scenario: Custom output path is used\n- **GIVEN** the user passes `--output \"/tmp/packed-agent\"`\n- **WHEN** `PackRuntime._prepare_output_path` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return `/tmp/packed-agent` as the output path, creating intermediate directories if needed\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Pack error handling — verbose vs non-verbose\n\n#### Scenario: Pack failure without verbose\n- **GIVEN** `PackRuntime.pack` raises an exception\n- **WHEN** the user did NOT pass `--verbose` on the `pack` subcommand\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL print `Error packaging agent: {e}` in red (no traceback) and exit with code `1`\n\n#### Scenario: Global verbose vs subcommand verbose\n- **GIVEN** the user passed `-v` on the root callback but NOT `--verbose` on `pack`\n- **WHEN** an error occurs during pack\n- **THEN** the traceback SHALL NOT be printed because `_handle_error` receives the subcommand's `verbose` flag which is `False`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Port validation via Pydantic\n\n#### Scenario: Port within valid range accepted\n- **GIVEN** the user passes `--port 8080`\n- **WHEN** `AgentMetadata` validators run (via `validate_port`)\n- **THEN** the port SHALL be accepted (range 1–65535)\n\n#### Scenario: Port below valid range rejected\n- **GIVEN** the user passes `--port 0`\n- **WHEN** `AgentMetadata` validators run (via `validate_port`)\n- **THEN** Pydantic SHALL raise `ValidationError` rejecting the invalid port\n\n#### Scenario: Port above valid range rejected\n- **GIVEN** the user passes `--port 70000`\n- **WHEN** `AgentMetadata` validators run (via `validate_port`)\n- **THEN** Pydantic SHALL raise `ValidationError` rejecting the invalid port\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Build mode validation via Pydantic\n\n#### Scenario: Valid build mode \"local\" accepted\n- **GIVEN** the user passes `--build-mode \"local\"`\n- **WHEN** `AgentMetadata` validators run (via `validate_build_mode`)\n- **THEN** the build mode SHALL be accepted and normalized to lowercase\n\n#### Scenario: Valid build mode \"cloud\" accepted\n- **GIVEN** the user passes `--build-mode \"cloud\"`\n- **WHEN** `AgentMetadata` validators run (via `validate_build_mode`)\n- **THEN** the build mode SHALL be accepted and normalized to lowercase\n\n#### Scenario: Invalid build mode rejected\n- **GIVEN** the user passes `--build-mode \"hybrid\"`\n- **WHEN** `AgentMetadata` validators run (via `validate_build_mode`)\n- **THEN** Pydantic SHALL raise `ValidationError` rejecting the unsupported build mode\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Language validation via Pydantic\n\n#### Scenario: Unsupported language rejected\n- **GIVEN** the user passes `--language \"nodejs\"`\n- **WHEN** `AgentMetadata` validators run (via `validate_language`)\n- **THEN** Pydantic SHALL raise `ValidationError` rejecting the unsupported language (only `python` and `java` allowed)\n\n#### Scenario: Language case normalization\n- **GIVEN** the user passes `--language \"Python\"`\n- **WHEN** `AgentMetadata` validators run (via `validate_language`)\n- **THEN** the language SHALL be accepted and normalized to `\"python\"`\n\n---\n\n## File changes\n\n| File | Action | Description |\n|------|--------|-------------|\n| `agentcube/cli/main.py` | Modify | `pack` command implementation with Typer options and error handling |\n| `agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py` | Modify | `PackRuntime` class with all pack lifecycle methods |\n| `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | Modify | `MetadataService.load_metadata` with fallback chain |\n| `agentcube/models/pack_models.py` | Modify | `MetadataOptions` dataclass for CLI option merging |\n| `agentcube/services/docker_service.py` | Modify | Dockerfile generation helpers if not already present |\n","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-020/delta-spec.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-020/delta-spec.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-020/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775850001167,"end":1775850001185}}}}
